race.comment: POCKET RAIDER (2) missed the frame two back but wound up strongly last time, finishing on late when third (19.79) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Form here at the trip sound including four wins. Can go on with it. HOPE'S TREASURE (8) is better than last start when fourth (19.88) in a Grade 4/5 at this track over 350m. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Likely to play a prominent role. CAMBRIDGE KING (5) shapes well for this on his convincing win a few runs back, getting around this track over 350m in 19.78 then hitting the frame in both runs since. Smart winner three back and looks a key chance on that form. BIG BANG BUSTER (4) picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again.
